---
title: Sizzlin' Saigon Steak Bowls with Sriracha-Lime Mayo and Jasmine Rice
description: There are few things more satisfying than steak for dinner. Until now! These beefy bowls are hearty, filling, and most of all—absolutely delicious. There’s tender steak simmered with garlic and soy sauce piled atop fluffy white rice along with a pickley cucumber salad and lime-spiked sriracha mayo. For a finishing touch, everything is sprinkled with chopped peanuts. One bite will have you totally bowled over.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sizzlin-saigon-steak-bowls-55aa81ad.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sizzlin-saigon-steak-bowls-5dc0485c96a80f298862f05f-e3149b15.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sizzlin-saigon-steak-bowls-5dc0485c96a80f298862f05f
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
cuisine: Vietnamese
nutrition:
  calories: 780 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1090 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add half the garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup} and @water{1 1/4%cups}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim and halve @Persian cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves and stems. Quarter @lime{1}. Thinly slice @chili pepper{1}.

In a medium #bowl{}, toss together cucumber, @shredded carrots{4%oz}, half the cilantro, a drizzle of oil, and juice from half the lime. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add @sugar{1/2%tsp} and toss to combine.

In a small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime juice, and @sriracha{1%tsp} to taste. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Once rice is done, pat @diced steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and remaining garlic; cook until steak is cooked almost to desired doneness, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @soy sauce{2%tbsp} and cook, stirring, until liquid has reduced and steak reaches desired doneness, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide between #bowls{} and top with diced steak and salad. Drizzle with sriracha-lime mayo. Garnish with remaining cilantro, @peanuts{1/2%oz}(chopped), and chili to taste.

> This recipe serves 2. Double all ingredients for 4 servings.